text: NFL games have 60 minutes of playing time with about 12 minutes of action in the average game. Wall to wall commercials and too many stoppages. Rugby league, rugby union and Aussie rules don’t do that. (Scrums in rugby union, however, can be quite tedious.)

text: American here and I love rugby league. You can catch selected @NRL and @SuperLeague games on @FOXSoccerPlus here in the states. They also air @AFL games. I prefer league, union and Aussie rules football over gridiron any day of the week.

text: I don't speak for the entire NRA, but I support universal background checks, for example. And I'm certainly open to conversations about what weapons should be banned, magazine sizes, etc. One problem is, no one on either "side" trusts the other side to negotiate in good faith.
author: ShaneRaynor

text: especially one with even a fraction of the NRA's influence. (There are actually some 2A groups that consider the @NRA too moderate!) So I stay a member. And I try to keep an open mind and engage in healthy discussions about gun violence, gun rights and gun safety.
author: ShaneRaynor

text: But I believe the @NRA does much good, especially in the areas of training and gun safety. Most NRA members are good people, and frankly, there's no "moderate" 2A organization to speak of...
author: ShaneRaynor

text: I don't like the @NRA's rigidity on some things, but this is actually part of our wider no compromise, no moderation, tribalist culture. I dislike that too. Sometimes I get frustrated and seriously consider relinquishing my membership.
author: ShaneRaynor

text: I'm uncomfortable with some aspects of gun culture, and I'm not the gun enthusiast some members are. And the tone of the @NRA bothers me quite often. (Plus, their fundraising is annoying as hell.)
author: ShaneRaynor

text: if such restrictions are upheld by the Courts. As for which weapons are restricted ... that should be part of an ongoing (civil!) conversation. I'm a member of the @NRA... a life member, in fact. That doesn't mean I agree with the NRA or its leadership on everything.
author: ShaneRaynor
